to Hillary Clinton's.

23:15.527 --> 23:21.967 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first: Latest figures from
Save the Children
show that nearly 13,000 children
have been

23:22.067 --> 23:28.040 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
rescued so far this year while
trying to cross
the Mediterranean from North
Africa to Italy.

23:28.140 --> 23:33.746 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Of those, more than 11,000 are
unaccompanied
and under the age of 18.

23:33.846 --> 23:39.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the second of his reports
from the Aquarius,
a ship run by Doctors Without
Borders, or

23:39.285 --> 23:46.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MSF, and SOS Mediterranee,
special correspondent
Malcolm Brabant looks at the
plight of women

23:46.325 --> 23:49.395 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and children on these high seas.

23:49.495 --> 23:55.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: This serene
night watch on
the bridge of the Aquarius
marked the end

23:55.701 --> 24:00.306 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of a week when strong winds and
high waves
had prevented rafts from
launching from the

24:00.406 --> 24:04.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Libyan coast. But as the sea
calmed down,
a flotilla left the Libyan
beaches and this

24:05.077 --> 24:06.845 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
boat was quickly in trouble.

24:06.945 --> 24:13.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: I think, at the moment,
it's reported
that 26 women and five children,
six of the

24:14.086 --> 24:15.821 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
26 women.

24:15.921 --> 24:22.594 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Initially,
rescuers thought
this woman wasn't breathing. One
day, these

24:22.695 --> 24:29.735 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
babies and toddlers will be told
just how
close they came to death. They
were soaked

24:29.835 --> 24:32.004 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in petrol from leaking canisters
for the outboard
engine.

24:32.104 --> 24:37.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mixed with saltwater, the fuel
causes serious
burns. The traffickers'
callousness extended

24:37.343 --> 24:42.047 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to denying the children life
jackets. Revived,
the patient was told to quickly
shower the

24:42.147 --> 24:44.650 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
petrol off her skin to avoid
burns.

24:44.750 --> 24:51.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: They are all crying. The
kids are screaming.
They're babies. And the women
seem quite in

24:51.657 --> 24:53.692 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
shock.

24:53.792 --> 24:59.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Still nauseous
from the fumes,
mothers, sisters, and daughters
were too overwhelmed

24:59.164 --> 25:04.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to recognize that after enduring
the Sahara
Desert, the anarchy of Libya and
the capriciousness

25:04.837 --> 25:10.609 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the waves, they had just
stepped back through
the portal of humanity.

25:10.709 --> 25:15.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: Everybody is infested
with fuel. The
smell of fuel is gigantic.
People are suffocating

25:15.948 --> 25:22.087 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because of the fumes. And people
are wet.
There's no food. There's no
water, and the

25:22.187 --> 25:30.062 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
quality of the boat is far below
average.
So they're lucky.

25:30.162 --> 25:36.802 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Within an hour
of being rescued,
Manuela, a 2-year-old, who was
always dancing

25:36.902 --> 25:41.607 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on land, is dancing again below
deck, testimony
to the resilience of children.

25:41.707 --> 25:46.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Although too young to understand
the nature
of their salvation, the kids
instinctively

25:46.412 --> 25:52.451 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
responded to the protective
atmosphere of
the air-conditioned women and
children's sanctuary,

25:52.551 --> 25:55.954 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
separated from the men.

25:56.054 --> 25:59.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
International relief agencies
say they're
extremely concerned about the
major upswing

25:59.825 --> 26:04.496 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the number of children who
are making this
most perilous of journeys. The
voyage between

26:04.596 --> 26:10.502 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Turkey and Greece is bad enough,
but this
one is many, many, many times
worse. Among

26:10.602 --> 26:13.572 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
those risking their lives are
unaccompanied
minors.

26:13.672 --> 26:19.478 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Inside, in one of the areas
behind me, there
are three boys who are less than
12 years

26:19.578 --> 26:26.552 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
old. And because of
international child protection
procedures, we're not able to
talk to them

26:26.652 --> 26:28.554 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
about their ordeal.

26:28.654 --> 26:34.026 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MSF's coordinator on the
Aquarius, Ferry Schippers,
shares the views of the U.N.'s
children fund,

26:34.126 --> 26:39.364 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
UNICEF, that unaccompanied
minors face abuse,
exploitation and death every
step of their

26:39.465 --> 26:41.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
journey.

26:41.233 --> 26:43.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FERRY SCHIPPERS, Doctors Without
Borders:
They're exploited on shore,
forced to work

26:43.802 --> 26:50.542 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to earn some money to pay for
passage. It's
easier to force younger people
to do something.

26:50.642 --> 26:59.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They're picked up by armed
individual groups,
unscrupulous men, and they are
put into so-called

26:59.651 --> 27:04.556 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
detention centers, old
factories, old warehouse.
They are beaten, mistreated.

27:04.656 --> 27:13.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Out on deck,
Manuela is reunited
with her father. In the
sanctuary, midwife

27:13.799 --> 27:18.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Angi Perri is checking on the
pregnant mothers
and providing them with the
first basic health

27:18.570 --> 27:20.606 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
care many of them have received
in months.

27:20.706 --> 27:24.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANGI PERRI, Midwife: They are
tried. They
came with a lot of shock. They
were crying

27:24.977 --> 27:31.116 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
all together. But after taking a
shower, we
reassured them that the
situation I think

27:31.216 --> 27:33.018 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is very stable and very, very
nice.

27:33.118 --> 27:35.287 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: How lucky do
you think they
were?

27:35.387 --> 27:41.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANGI PERRI: They were very, very
lucky because
the trip tonight was a trip that
we consider

27:41.727 --> 27:47.132 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
risky, because the weather
wasn't really good
in the past days. Now they have
food. They

27:47.232 --> 27:54.273 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
can recover very easily. So they
were lucky,
because the risk of traveling in
the sea with

27:54.373 --> 28:01.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a rubber boat is very high
always. So this
is very nice. For me, I am very
happy today.

28:01.947 --> 28:06.652 align:left position:25%,start line:73.33% size:75%
MALCOLM BRABANT:
Twenty-seven-year-old Sophie
Agbo comes from Cameroon, a West
African country

28:06.752 --> 28:11.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that has problems with the Boko
Haram Islamist
group, and also economic
hardship.

28:11.390 --> 28:21.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SOPHIE AGBO, Refugee: I left
Cameroon, because,
in Cameroon, there's not -- I
wanted to go

28:21.934 --> 28:26.104 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
out to come and find -- to look
for my future.

28:26.204 --> 28:30.976 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Two hours after
being plucked
from the sea, she's had time to
reflect on

28:31.076 --> 28:32.844 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the dangers of the journey.

28:32.945 --> 28:40.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SOPHIE AGBO: I don't know that I
can describe
it, but the journey was very
bad. But thank

28:41.019 --> 28:47.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
God for that. I just thank God,
because the
God that took me from Cameroon
to here, I

28:48.026 --> 28:51.630 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
just appreciate, to give the
glory and honor
to him.

28:51.730 --> 28:56.368 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Maria from
Ivory Coast could
only give single-word answers
about her desperate

28:56.468 --> 29:01.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
journey, but her mother, who
wanted to be
identified as Fatima, claimed
she has been

29:01.573 --> 29:03.842 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
calm throughout, fortified by
her faith.

29:03.942 --> 29:08.580 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
FATIMA, Refugee (through
translator): When
I was at sea, I prayed to God to
allow us

29:08.680 --> 29:13.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to triumph and to save us. We
could not have
arrived without the help of the
savior. We

29:13.752 --> 29:16.188 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
have the savior, and we have
been saved.

29:16.288 --> 29:21.360 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: But at the far
end of the
sanctuary, 22-year-old Aseman,
who is due

29:21.460 --> 29:25.964 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to give birth to a son in two
months' time,
was more forthcoming. She had
traveled from

29:26.064 --> 29:30.068 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Eritrea, sometimes described as
the North
Korea of Africa.

29:30.168 --> 29:35.240 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ASEMAN, Refugee (through
translator): I am
so happy to be safely on board
this ship.

29:35.340 --> 29:40.278 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Recently, many Eritreans
capsized. About 700
or 800 came by wooden boat. A
lot of our brothers

29:40.379 --> 29:43.682 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and sisters died. But we took a
small rubber
boat, which is very dangerous.

29:43.782 --> 29:48.387 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I am so fortunate and happy to
survive. I
wouldn't advise anyone to risk
taking this

29:48.487 --> 29:52.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
journey because there are so
many problems.
But people are obliged to leave
their country,

29:53.058 --> 29:56.928 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because they have no choice. If
the Eritrean
government were to introduce
democracy and

29:57.029 --> 30:00.298 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
decent living standards, then it
would be
preferable to stay.

30:00.399 --> 30:05.203 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Their stay on
the Aquarius
ended quickly, as they were
transferred to

30:05.303 --> 30:09.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
another boat that would take
them and other
migrants to Italy. Their gamble
paid off,

30:09.641 --> 30:11.410 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
just.

30:11.510 --> 30:16.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now they face a battle for
acceptance in a
Europe that has no solutions to
the exodus

30:16.381 --> 30:21.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from Africa. They leave behind a
sea that
for most Europeans is a holiday
paradise.

30:22.087 --> 30:24.923 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Out here, it's another world.

30:25.023 --> 30:30.996 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," this is
Malcolm Brabant
off the Libyan coast.

30:31.096 --> 30:45.110 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Next: a big
shakeup in television
news, and a media and political
bombshell,

30:45.210 --> 30:48.914 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as Roger Ailes is ousted as the
head of FOX
News.

30:49.014 --> 30:50.782 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Jeffrey Brown reports.

30:50.882 --> 30:55.520 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: It all unfolded
quickly, in
a matter of weeks, after former
FOX anchor

30:55.620 --> 31:00.859 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Gretchen Carlson filed a sexual
harassment
suit against Roger Ailes,
longtime head of

31:00.959 --> 31:02.794 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
FOX News.

31:02.894 --> 31:07.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ailes denied the charges. But
21st Century
Fox, the cable network's parent
company, hired

31:07.966 --> 31:13.905 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
a law firm to conduct an
investigation. According
to Carlson's lawyers, 20 or more
other women

31:14.005 --> 31:20.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
then came forward with claims
about Ailes'
conduct, including Megyn Kelly,
one of the

31:20.545 --> 31:22.481 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
network's star anchors.

31:22.581 --> 31:28.720 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Publicly, many other prominent
on-air personalities
at FOX, including Bill O'Reilly,
Sean Hannity,

31:28.820 --> 31:34.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and Greta Van Susteren, backed
Ailes and said
they were unaware of any
inappropriate behavior.

31:34.893 --> 31:39.998 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Rupert Murdoch issued a
statement late yesterday
without referring to the
harassment charges,

31:40.098 --> 31:45.871 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
saying that: "Roger Ailes has
made a remarkable
contribution to our company and
our country.

31:45.971 --> 31:51.409 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Roger shared my vision of a
great and independent
television organization and
executed it brilliantly

31:51.510 --> 31:54.312 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
over 20 great years."

31:54.412 --> 32:00.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Roger Ailes, now 76, has been an
influential
figure for decades in Republican
politics,

32:00.385 --> 32:07.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as an adviser and strategist to
Presidents
Nixon, Reagan and George H.W.
Bush. He created

32:07.325 --> 32:11.696 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FOX News 20 years ago and built
it into the
most-watched cable news channel.

32:11.797 --> 32:15.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRIT HUME, FOX News: More news
is on the way,
fair, balanced and unafraid.

32:15.267 --> 32:21.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Promoted as an
alternative
to traditional mainstream media.
It has been

32:21.139 --> 32:25.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a huge moneymaker for its parent
company,
and a target for critics of its
conservative

32:25.977 --> 32:27.746 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
tone and team.

32:27.846 --> 32:31.483 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Ailes said this in a 2004
interview with C-SPAN'S
Brian Lamb:

32:31.583 --> 32:33.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROGER AILES, Former FOX News
Executive: Well,
we have changed the business a
little bit.

32:33.385 --> 32:39.491 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think FOX News has come on the
scene and
identified itself as fair and
balanced. We

32:39.591 --> 32:46.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
try to do that every day. I
think others,
instead of trying to get more
fair and balanced,

32:46.398 --> 32:49.568 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
probably are offended by that or
worried about
it.

32:49.668 --> 32:54.472 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Rupert Murdoch
and his sons,
James and Lachlan, will now
decide on a successor

32:54.573 --> 32:58.844 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to Roger Ailes and the future of
the network
he built.

32:58.944 --> 33:03.682 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And joining me now, Jane Hall, a
journalism
professor at American University
who previously

33:03.782 --> 33:09.287 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
served as a media reporter for
The Los Angeles
Times and commentator at FOX
News, and Ken

33:09.387 --> 33:15.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Doctor, who writes on the media
business for
Politico and on his blog,
Newsonomics.

33:15.327 --> 33:16.061 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Welcome to both of you.

33:16.161 --> 33:18.129 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Ken, let me start with you.

33:18.230 --> 33:24.236 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You watched this all unfold. Was
it the accumulation
of charges? What in the end led
to Roger Ailes

33:24.336 --> 33:25.203 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
being ousted?

33:25.303 --> 33:27.105 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KEN DOCTOR, Newsonomics: It was.
It was.

33:27.205 --> 33:32.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's an extraordinary event,
as you laid
out, and it's almost operatic to
have it happen,

33:32.744 --> 33:39.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the final parting, on the day of
the Trump
acceptance. It was a
culmination. It was clearly

33:39.684 --> 33:47.058 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a frat boy kind of culture that
has been characteristic
of FOX News for a long time, and
that's not

33:47.158 --> 33:49.294 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
going to change overnight.

33:49.394 --> 33:53.632 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So now the Murdochs are going to
have to face
that question. And we know the
Murdoch sons

33:53.732 --> 33:59.037 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are in charge of the business
for the first
time. Roger Ailes had kind of
